  "bio_raw": "Anika Shah is an early-career researcher and writer who explores the intersections of popular culture, literature, gender and sexuality, and affect, emotion, and embodiment through the lens of feminist cultural studies. She holds a PhD from the University of Technology Sydney (UTS) for her dissertation\nUnpacking the Closet: Queer Disclosures from Bangladesh\n. Beyond academia, she writes, translates, and edits fiction and non-fiction across a diversity of creative platforms. As a researcher and creative practitioner, she is intrigued by projects that juxtapose both terrains.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Gender and Sexuality; Studies of Popular Culture and Literature; Affect, Emotion and Embodiment."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPhD, Cultural Studies\n, University of Technology Sydney, Australia\nMA, Literatures in English and Cultural Studies\n, Jahangirnagar University, Bangladesh\nBA, English Literature\n, Jahangirnagar University, Bangladesh"
    }
  ],
